        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 23 at 5:54PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 554 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Ubly to near Cass City to near Vassar.
Movement was east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Strong thunderstorms will be near...
Caro, Cass City, and Ubly around 600 PM EDT.
Argyle around 610 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by these storms include Ruth, Tyre,
Parisville, Palms, Deford, Helena, Wilmot, Ivanhoe, Minden, and
Watrousville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
